sql:
SELECT MAX(action_count) AS max_action_count
FROM (
  SELECT page_id, COUNT(action_id) AS action_count
  FROM actions
  GROUP BY page_id
) AS page_action_counts;

external_knowledge:
- The average session duration is calculated in days;
- The top 5 actions are determined by the frequency of their occurrence;
- The top 5 active users are determined by the number of sessions they have participated in.

- "guardians of the digital realm" refers to users with the role 'admin';
- "actions" are the activities or operations performed by users during their sessions;
- "sessions" are periods of user activity, defined by start and end times.

sql:
SELECT AVG(actions_count) AS average_steps_per_session
FROM (
  SELECT COUNT(action_id) AS actions_count
  FROM actions
  GROUP BY session_id
);

