sql:
SELECT MAX(action_count) AS max_actions
FROM (
  SELECT session_id, COUNT(action_id) AS action_count
  FROM actions
  GROUP BY session_id
) AS action_counts;

external_knowledge:
- "top three most active users" refers to users with the highest number of actions;
- "actions" are recorded in the `actions` table and are associated with user sessions;
- "roles" and "device types" are attributes of users and user sessions, respectively.

- "leading role" refers to the user with the highest number of actions in their role;
- "department" refers to the role within the organization;
- "stars shine the brightest" refers to the top users who have performed the most actions in their roles.
